# Library Card JavaCard Project Structure

This is a **JavaCard-based Library Management System** using JCardSim simulator.

## Architecture Layers

### Applet Layer (`card_gui/src/applet/`)
JavaCard applet code running on the simulated card:
- [LibraryCardApplet.java](mdc:card_gui/src/applet/LibraryCardApplet.java) - Main applet router
- [AppletConstants.java](mdc:card_gui/src/applet/AppletConstants.java) - APDU constants, field lengths
- [PinManager.java](mdc:card_gui/src/applet/PinManager.java) - PIN operations with PBKDF2
- [CardInfoManager.java](mdc:card_gui/src/applet/CardInfoManager.java) - Card info storage (ID, Name, Date)
- [BookManager.java](mdc:card_gui/src/applet/BookManager.java) - Book borrowing

### Service Layer (`card_gui/src/service/`)
- [SimulatorService.java](mdc:card_gui/src/service/SimulatorService.java) - Bridge between GUI and applet

### GUI Layer (`card_gui/src/pages/`)
- [SettingsPage.java](mdc:card_gui/src/pages/SettingsPage.java) - Card creation and management

### Models (`card_gui/src/models/`)
- [CardInfo.java](mdc:card_gui/src/models/CardInfo.java) - Card data model (6 fields)
- [BorrowedBook.java](mdc:card_gui/src/models/BorrowedBook.java) - Book model

## Key Entry Points
- Run `main()` in [LibraryCardMainFrame.java](mdc:card_gui/src/LibraryCardMainFrame.java)

## Important Limitation
**JCardSim does not persist data.** All card data is lost when app closes.
